Vocablary : 

stale - no longer fresh or pleasant 
holy grail : vessel to drink.. high respect 
intricate - very complicated or detailed 
decision curve - 
wiggle 
erratic - not even or regular in pattern
daunting - seems difficult to deal with in prospect  / frighten
conflate  - combine (two or more sets of information, texts, ideas, etc.) into one.
ensemble - a group of items viewed as a whole rather than individually
indicted - formally accused for a charge of chrime
Immunity from prosecution is a doctrine of international law that allows an accused to avoid prosecution for criminal offences.
skeptical  - not easily convinced, having doubts 
repercussion - an unintended consequence of an event or action, an unwanted one
insincere - false, fake
gratification - pleasure, especially when gained from the satisfaction of a desire.
epiphany - a moment of sudden and great revelation or realization.
a measure of the relation between the mean value of one variable (e.g. output) and corresponding values of other variables (e.g. time and cost).
Heuristic - any approach to problem solving, learning, or discovery that employs a practical method, not guaranteed to be optimal, perfect, logical,
arsenal - a collection of weapons or military equipments 
cliffhanger - a dramatic and exciting ending to an episode of a serial, leaving the audience in suspense and anxious not to miss the next episode.
hassle - irritating inconvenience
obliterate - destroy everything/wipeout
realm - kingdom/domain
spurious - bogus/  fake /illegitimate
appalling - terrible or vary bad



